        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 6:26AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 625 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 12 miles northwest of Walhalla to 9 miles south of
Clayton to 6 miles south of Cleveland. Movement was east at 25 mph.
An isolated thunderstorm may develop along the line.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Long Creek, Jocassee Gorges, Cornelia, Devils Fork State Park, Alto,
Salem, Tallulah Gorge State Park, Demorest, Lake Rabun, and Mountain
Rest.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
